    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using a terminal frontend, `UILeave` is not triggered when exiting after any number of `:restart` calls. Perhaps notable, but `UILeave` is still triggered with subsequent `:restart`s; this behavior only appears when properly exiting Neovim.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1) Create `/tmp/init.lua` with the following contents:\n   ```lua\n   vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"UIEnter\" }, { callback = function()\n     local file = io.open(\"/tmp/nvim-ui.log\", \"a\")\n     file:write(\"UIEnter triggered\\n\")\n     file:flush()\n     file:close()    \n   end })\n   vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"UILeave\" }, { callback = function()\n     local file = io.open(\"/tmp/nvim-ui.log\", \"a\")\n     file:write(\"UILeave triggered\\n\")\n     file:flush()\n     file:close()    \n   end })\n   ```\n2) Run with:\n   ```sh\n   nvim --clean -u /tmp/init.lua  \n   ```\n3) In Neovim, run `:restart`, then `:q`\n4) Inspect `/tmp/nvim-ui.log` contents:\n   ```\n   UIEnter triggered\n   UILeave triggered\n   UIEnter triggered\n   ```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`UILeave` should be triggered on exit after `:restart`, like it is normally; steps 2-4 can be run without calling `:restart` and `UILeave triggered` will appear in the output as expected.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty 0.46.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
