            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Odd workaround: spawn a child process that still exists when `:q` is run:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"UIEnter\" }, { callback = function()\n  local file = io.open(\"/tmp/nvim-ui.log\", \"a\")\n  file:write(\"UIEnter triggered\\n\")\n  file:flush()\n  file:close()\nend })\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"UILeave\" }, { callback = function()\n  local file = io.open(\"/tmp/nvim-ui.log\", \"a\")\n  file:write(\"UILeave triggered\\n\")\n  file:flush()\n  file:close()\nend })\nvim.fn.jobstart({ 'cat' })\n```",
